 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# SOM Training on IRIS Dataset\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import load_iris\n",
    "from fastsom import *"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Creating the DataBunch"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def iris():\n",
    "    \"Loads the IRIS dataset into two tensors.\"\n",
    "    iris = load_iris()\n",
    "    x = torch.tensor(iris.data)\n",
    "    y = torch.tensor(iris.target)\n",
    "    labels = iris.feature_names\n",
    "    target_names = iris.target_names\n",
    "    return x, y, labels, target_names"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y, labels, target_names = iris()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's create an `UnsupervisedDataBunch` with shuffle sampling and variance+std normalization:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "db = UnsupervisedDataBunch((x, y), valid=0.05, sampler='shuffle', normalizer='var', bs=50)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(tensor([ 1.6997e-15,  7.3103e-16, -4.5504e-16,  3.9561e-16],\n",
       "        dtype=torch.float64),\n",
       " tensor([1.0000, 1.0000, 1.0000, 1.0000], dtype=torch.float64))"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "d = db.train_ds.tensors[0]\n",
    "d.mean(0), d.std(0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Creating the Learner\n",
    "\n",
    "The `SomLearner` class can automatically infer the number of features from the `DataBunch`, and has a default map size of 10x10.\n",
    "\n",
    "Since IRIS is a small dataset, we might want to use a smaller map:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "size = (8, 8)\n",
    "\n",
    "learn = SomLearner(db,\n",
    "    size=size,\n",
    "    lr=[0.6, 0.3, 0.1], \n",
    "    metrics=[topologic_err],\n",
    "    visualize=['weights', 'bmus'],\n",
    "    trainer=ExperimentalSomTrainer)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Training the model"
   ]
  },

   "execution_count": 7,

       "            fig.waiting = false;\n",
       "            return;\n",

       "            return;\n",

       "                // console.log(\"Handling '\" + msg_type + \"' message: \", msg);\n",

       "// from http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1114465/getting-mouse-location-in-canvas\n",

       "mpl.toolbar_items = [[\"Home\", \"Reset original view\", \"fa fa-home icon-home\", \"home\"], [\"Back\", \"Back to previous view\", \"fa fa-arrow-left icon-arrow-left\", \"back\"], [\"Forward\", \"Forward to next view\", \"fa fa-arrow-right icon-arrow-right\", \"forward\"], [\"\", \"\", \"\", \"\"], [\"Pan\", \"Pan axes with left mouse, zoom with right\", \"fa fa-arrows icon-move\", \"pan\"], [\"Zoom\", \"Zoom to rectangle\", \"fa fa-square-o icon-check-empty\", \"zoom\"], [\"\", \"\", \"\", \"\"], [\"Download\", \"Download plot\", \"fa fa-floppy-o icon-save\", \"download\"]];\n",

       "mpl.default_extension = \"png\";var comm_websocket_adapter = function(comm) {\n",

       "\n",
       "mpl.find_output_cell = function(html_output) {\n",
       "    // Return the cell and output element which can be found *uniquely* in the notebook.\n",
       "    // Note - this is a bit hacky, but it is done because the \"notebook_saving.Notebook\"\n",
       "    // IPython event is triggered only after the cells have been serialised, which for\n",
       "    // our purposes (turning an active figure into a static one), is too late.\n",
       "    var cells = IPython.notebook.get_cells();\n",
       "    var ncells = cells.length;\n",
       "    for (var i=0; i<ncells; i++) {\n",
       "        var cell = cells[i];\n",
       "        if (cell.cell_type === 'code'){\n",
       "            for (var j=0; j<cell.output_area.outputs.length; j++) {\n",
       "                var data = cell.output_area.outputs[j];\n",
       "                if (data.data) {\n",
       "                    // IPython >= 3 moved mimebundle to data attribute of output\n",
       "                    data = data.data;\n",
       "                }\n",
       "                if (data['text/html'] == html_output) {\n",
       "                    return [cell, data, j];\n",
       "                }\n",
       "            }\n",
       "        }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "}\n",
